history.content: You aren't guaranteed any seats in upper division classes.

See http://www.eecs.berkeley.edu/Policies/enrollment.shtml .  The student above is correct that there aren't any guarantees but the department does want you to be able to take courses or interest and move towards your degree. You also have to show you prioritize those goals by using phase 1 and phase 2 of telebears to indicate that in accordance with the procedures linked to above.

I am a declared LSCS senior standing student. I plan to take 160 and 186 in Spring 16 which are very popular and impacted. However, I also major in Statistics which has some quite impacted courses as well. Should I use phase I units to reserve myself a seat in 160 and 186? Or will I be guaranteed to be enrolled in 160 and 186 because of my senior standing and CS declared? Also, I still haven't completed EE 16A yet. I plan to take it later or during summer, but the rumor says it is very very popular. Should I try to finish it early? I look for some suggestions and thank you all in advance!
history.subject: Phase I units
